  "publisher": "anime",
  "about": "Full Name: Richehlette\nAge: 10-12\nGender: Female\nBirthday: March 15\nHair: Sky Blue\nEyes: Sky Blue\nOccupation: Witch Apprentice\nAffiliation: Pointed Cap Witches\nResidence: Qifrey's Atelier\nSpecialty: Richeh's Magic, Crystal Magic, Small Seals\nStatus:\n\nRicheh is a young apprentice witch and a disciple of Qifrey. \n\nRicheh was born in the Great Hall to a family of witches. Four years before the events of the manga, Richeh requested to apprentice alongside her brother, Riliphin. She joined Qifrey's atelier after breaking off her apprenticeship with her first master.\n\nRicheh has a seemingly emotionless and childish personality, being very stubborn, individualistic, and resentful of authority figures that tell her what to do.[citation needed] She often refers to herself in the third person, another facet of her childlike personality. She is opposed to the idea of growing up and wishes to stay as she is forever in order to maintain her unique magic and individuality.\n\nShe specializes in crystal magic, particularly creating transparent crystal ribbons. She also excels at drawing small, intricate seals, even being able to use such tiny seals to form window-ways. Her individualistic magic style is expressed in her more out of the box solutions to problems and tests.\n\nRather than a typical Japanese pronoun, Richeh tends to refer to herself using her own nickname, リチェ (Riche). This lends a rather childish quality to her speech, in keeping with her aversion to growing up.\n\n(Source: Witch Hat Atelier Independent Wiki)",
  "note": null,
  "source": "anime"
